Package InfrastructureManager.ModuleManagement

Interface PlatformOutput

All Known Implementing Classes:
AdvantEdgeClient, ConsoleOutput, FileOutput, GETOutput, MatchMakerOutput, ModuleController, NetworkOutput, NodeLimitOutput, ParametrizedGETOutput, ScenarioDispatcher, ScenarioEditor, SSHClient
public interface PlatformOutput
Interface that defines an output for the Edge Diagnostics Platform. Outputs are components that allow the platform to interact with and control its environment by triggering events of different nature. Classes that act as an output for the platform should not only implement this interface but also extend the PlatformObject class (or one of its module specific subclasses)

    • execute

      void execute​(java.lang.String response) throws ModuleExecutionException

      Parameters:

      Throws:
      ModuleExecutionException - If an error occurs during execution.

      PlatformModule.ModuleState getOwnerModuleState()
      Returns the state of the owner module. Is important to avoid triggering outputs in paused modules
